div1.p: IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE 9th JUSTICE CIRCUIT, WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF L.J. URANN FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.} EXCEPTIONS
And come now the petitioner, L.J. Urann, and excepts to the return of L.C. Smith, Sheriff of King County, Washington and custodian of the petitioner; upon the ground and for the reason as follows:
I.
That said return is not a return and does not state facts sufficient to constitute a proper return or to entitle the respondant to hold the prisoner.
II.
That said return or said certificate does not show that any crime was committed or that the petitioner was guilty of a felony.
III.
That said return or ceritficate does not set forth the law which is alleged to have been violated by the petitioner or any law of the State of Massachusetts.
IV.
That said return does not justify by any statement of fact the issuance of the warrant of the demanding State.
V.

That said return does not show that the petitioner is a fugitive from justice of the State of Massachusetts or that he was in the State of Massachusetts at the time that the alleged crime was committed.
VI.

That said return does not set forth any affidavit of the complaint of the prosecuting witness in the State of Massachusetts or any other showing which was made to the Governor which justifies or would justify the issuance of warrant by the Governor of Massachusetts.
Vince H. Faben Attorney for Petitioner.
Reed. Copy July 3rd 1905 Kenneth Mackeeboh
